This paper is about few-shot learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper proposes a meta-learning algorithm called Meta-SGD that can quickly adapt to new tasks with few examples. This topic is closely related to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.RO (Robotics). Among these sub-categories, cs.LG is the most likely one because the paper is primarily about machine learning, and few-shot learning is a subfield of machine learning. cs.AI and cs.CV are also likely because they are closely related to machine learning and often involve few-shot learning. cs.NE and cs.RO are less likely but still possible because they also involve learning algorithms and may have applications in few-shot learning.
